1
00:00:10,077 --> 00:00:11,443
Taxi!

2
00:00:11,512 --> 00:00:13,345
<i>Carpe diem.</i>

3
00:00:14,448 --> 00:00:16,849
That was hell.
Actual physical hell.

4
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:18,550
I think I went a tad overboard.

5
00:00:18,618 --> 00:00:20,785
<i>How annoying is carpe diem?</i>

6
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:22,054
A lot overboard.

7
00:00:22,122 --> 00:00:23,433
They took something from me.

8
00:00:23,457 --> 00:00:25,418
Yeah, that wasn't an exam.
That was an interrogation.

9
00:00:25,442 --> 00:00:27,926
Like, way, way overboard.

10
00:00:27,994 --> 00:00:29,739
The mind games. Trick questions.

11
00:00:29,763 --> 00:00:31,341
It felt like al-Qaeda in there.

12
00:00:31,365 --> 00:00:35,283
<i>How are you supposed to
plan a life, a career, a family,</i>

13
00:00:35,352 --> 00:00:37,970
<i>if you're always
carpe-ing the diem?</i>

14
00:00:38,038 --> 00:00:39,838
Next test is June.

15
00:00:39,907 --> 00:00:41,440
June's not bad.

16
00:00:41,508 --> 00:00:43,224
2013.

17
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,860
Oh.

18
00:00:44,929 --> 00:00:47,646
What's done is done. Let's just
not even talk about it anymore.

19
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,215
<i>If we all seized every
moment of every day,</i>

20
00:00:50,284 --> 00:00:51,633
<i>there wouldn't be doctors.</i>

21
00:00:51,719 --> 00:00:53,129
<i>Who would sit
through med school?</i>

22
00:00:53,153 --> 00:00:55,332
Anyone know how Alex did?

23
00:00:55,356 --> 00:00:57,083
Anyone know if Alex made it?

24
00:00:57,107 --> 00:00:58,107
Made it?

25
00:00:58,175 --> 00:01:00,215
What do you mean, "Made it"?

26
00:01:02,196 --> 00:01:04,762
<i>We'd all be too busy</i>

27
00:01:04,831 --> 00:01:07,265
<i>living in the now.</i>

28
00:01:07,318 --> 00:01:09,083
<i>Whatever that means.</i>

29
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:10,585
Hey.

30
00:01:11,372 --> 00:01:12,921
You okay?

31
00:01:13,724 --> 00:01:15,774
I'm not sure.

32
00:01:15,842 --> 00:01:18,393
I hope you're not
worried about last night.

33
00:01:18,462 --> 00:01:20,207
I'm not worried
about last night.

34
00:01:20,231 --> 00:01:22,508
I'm worried because I
checked with some of my friends

35
00:01:22,532 --> 00:01:24,299
on the committee,

36
00:01:24,368 --> 00:01:27,919
and one of your Seattle
Grace doctors didn't pass.

37
00:01:27,988 --> 00:01:29,287
Any idea who?

38
00:01:29,356 --> 00:01:32,407
They weren't sure.
But if it's Jackson,

39
00:01:32,493 --> 00:01:34,973
he'll blame me forever.

40
00:01:37,898 --> 00:01:39,565
Welcome to the
American Medical Board

41
00:01:39,633 --> 00:01:41,433
of Surgery Certifying
Examination.

42
00:01:41,502 --> 00:01:42,996
We'll give you four
separate scenarios

43
00:01:43,020 --> 00:01:44,786
in three 30-minute sessions,

44
00:01:44,855 --> 00:01:46,688
10-minute breaks in between.

45
00:01:46,757 --> 00:01:49,485
To pass the test, you must
pass two of the three sessions.

46
00:01:49,509 --> 00:01:51,303
Now, you can fail a
session and still pass.

47
00:01:51,327 --> 00:01:54,106
Still pass. But examiners
are not permitted to indicate

48
00:01:54,130 --> 00:01:56,781
whether you passed
or failed each session.

49
00:01:56,850 --> 00:02:00,235
You'll be rated on your ability
to diagnose, manage treatment,

50
00:02:00,304 --> 00:02:01,736
handle the unexpected,

51
00:02:01,805 --> 00:02:04,489
basically, the strength of
your constitution in crisis.

52
00:02:06,744 --> 00:02:11,229
And when we move
on to the next scenario,

53
00:02:11,298 --> 00:02:16,301
there's no doubling
back, meaning,

54
00:02:16,370 --> 00:02:18,247
once a question is asked...

55
00:02:18,271 --> 00:02:20,031
You can't go back.
Understood, sir.

56
00:02:22,726 --> 00:02:25,460
Are you in a hurry, Dr. Yang?

57
00:02:25,528 --> 00:02:28,263
No, sir. Just ready
when you are.

58
00:02:29,183 --> 00:02:30,448
Mm-hmm.

59
00:02:31,718 --> 00:02:35,353
So then, a 65-year-old woman

60
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:38,702
is being seen by her
primary care physician

61
00:02:38,726 --> 00:02:41,643
for a workup of osteoporosis

62
00:02:41,711 --> 00:02:45,130
when she is found to
have elevated calcium.

63
00:02:45,198 --> 00:02:48,500
Her PTH level was
well above normal.

64
00:02:48,569 --> 00:02:51,336
Her doctor sends her to you.

65
00:02:51,404 --> 00:02:54,217
Elevated calcium and
PTH would indicate

66
00:02:54,241 --> 00:02:55,824
primary hyperparathyroidism.

67
00:02:55,892 --> 00:02:58,052
I would offer the
patient a para...

68
00:02:58,795 --> 00:03:00,011
thyroidectomy.

69
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:01,858
And first, I would
explore the right side.

70
00:03:01,882 --> 00:03:03,248
If that gland is large...

71
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:05,884
I would biopsy it.

72
00:03:05,953 --> 00:03:09,287
After doing the
biopsy, I would...

73
00:03:09,356 --> 00:03:11,606
Hang on. What did the
pathologist's report say?

74
00:03:11,675 --> 00:03:15,137
Path comes back with
parathyroid hyperplasia.

75
00:03:15,161 --> 00:03:16,428
Uh, oh...

76
00:03:16,496 --> 00:03:18,330
And how large was the gland?

77
00:03:21,251 --> 00:03:23,611
How much longer are we
gonna give this Dr. Karev?

78
00:03:24,655 --> 00:03:26,304
Fifteen?

79
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:29,508
Next, I would resect it and
explore the other glands.

80
00:03:29,576 --> 00:03:32,493
Aggressive choice.

81
00:03:32,562 --> 00:03:37,332
Well, I suppose I could wait for
the IPM before taking further actions.

82
00:03:37,400 --> 00:03:38,766
Mm-hmm.

83
00:03:38,836 --> 00:03:41,156
Are you sure you're
okay with that?

84
00:03:45,659 --> 00:03:47,426
Yes, I'm okay with that.

85
00:03:48,662 --> 00:03:50,728
If the IPM

86
00:03:50,797 --> 00:03:53,398
showed PTH levels
in the normal range...

87
00:03:55,436 --> 00:03:57,151
Dr. Grey?

88
00:03:57,220 --> 00:03:59,660
I would feel comfortable
concluding the procedure.

89
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,367
Dude, there's no other way?

90
00:04:12,435 --> 00:04:14,453
Helicopter. Magic carpet.

91
00:04:14,521 --> 00:04:15,754
That lane is open.

92
00:04:15,823 --> 00:04:18,143
That's the bus lane. I
don't see any buses.

93
00:04:18,175 --> 00:04:19,852
I'll get a ticket.

94
00:04:19,876 --> 00:04:21,554
Come on, man. I'll give
you double any ticket.

95
00:04:21,578 --> 00:04:22,788
What about my insurance?

96
00:04:22,812 --> 00:04:24,463
Come on, man. Just
take the bus lane.

97
00:04:26,450 --> 00:04:28,161
Nah. How far are we?

98
00:04:28,185 --> 00:04:30,305
Twenty blocks, give or take.

99
00:04:34,508 --> 00:04:36,668
Catch the game last night?

100
00:04:36,844 --> 00:04:38,238
Come on, come on. Move.

101
00:04:38,262 --> 00:04:40,342
I heard it went 11 innings.

102
00:04:42,265 --> 00:04:44,105
Move! Move! Look out! Move!

103
00:04:46,136 --> 00:04:49,337
Come one, come on! Almost
there. Move, it's a hurry.

104
00:04:53,193 --> 00:04:54,970
Okay, who wants more pancakes?

105
00:04:54,994 --> 00:04:56,695
You haven't had any. Sit down.

106
00:04:56,763 --> 00:04:59,325
I can't sit still. He's
taking his test right now.

107
00:04:59,349 --> 00:05:02,300
It's cute, you being
nervous for Jackson.

108
00:05:02,369 --> 00:05:04,380
You want some more
juice? It's paternal.

109
00:05:04,404 --> 00:05:05,970
You're a natural father.

110
00:05:06,039 --> 00:05:08,484
Are you sure you don't want
anything? I could make some bacon...

111
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:10,258
We should have a baby.

112
00:05:14,264 --> 00:05:18,317
Don't freak out. I
mean, I like this.

113
00:05:18,385 --> 00:05:20,435
I like you, I like your kid,

114
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,103
and I like your
kid's moms. And I...

115
00:05:25,509 --> 00:05:28,042
You know, you don't have
to say anything right now.

116
00:05:28,111 --> 00:05:30,562
Just go back to
worrying about Jackson,

117
00:05:30,631 --> 00:05:33,031
and we can talk
about this later.

118
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:35,633
I would say no
rush, but, you know,

119
00:05:35,703 --> 00:05:37,919
actually, my FSH
levels would suggest that

120
00:05:37,988 --> 00:05:40,388
rushing a little might not be
the worst thing in the world.

121
00:05:52,085 --> 00:05:54,185
Julia wants to have
a baby with Mark.

122
00:05:54,254 --> 00:05:55,582
I can't even deal
with that right now.

123
00:05:55,606 --> 00:05:57,172
Wow.

124
00:05:57,240 --> 00:05:59,551
I should've picked him up myself.
I mean, what's wrong with me?

125
00:05:59,575 --> 00:06:02,143
Okay, I thought he was your
brother's best friend, not yours.

126
00:06:02,212 --> 00:06:05,914
We were all super close, and
he was my rock when Tim died.

127
00:06:05,983 --> 00:06:08,183
I just... Oh, God. I
let my rock take a cab.

128
00:06:08,218 --> 00:06:09,834
So you let him take a cab.

129
00:06:09,903 --> 00:06:11,848
Well, I mean, listen,
he just flew in from Tibet

130
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,355
and he has cancer.

131
00:06:13,423 --> 00:06:14,122
I mean, the least I
could do is pick him up at

132
00:06:14,191 --> 00:06:15,431
the baggage claim.

133
00:06:15,492 --> 00:06:17,492
Hey, hey, hey. Okay,
you need to chill out.

134
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:21,296
Look, I know that you're
worried, but as far as cancers go,

135
00:06:21,364 --> 00:06:22,798
I mean, his is
very slow-growing.

136
00:06:22,866 --> 00:06:24,644
He told you he found
out, what, six months ago?

137
00:06:24,668 --> 00:06:27,202
I mean, he could be fine.

138
00:06:27,271 --> 00:06:28,931
Yeah. Yeah.

139
00:06:28,955 --> 00:06:31,234
Well, with you in the
OR, I'm not worried.

140
00:06:31,258 --> 00:06:33,519
You're gonna love him,
and he's gonna love you.

141
00:06:33,543 --> 00:06:36,027
Well, I'm taking his tumor
out. It's the least he could do.

142
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:37,462
Phoenix.

143
00:06:37,830 --> 00:06:39,097
Nick!

144
00:06:40,901 --> 00:06:43,301
Hey. It's good to see you.

145
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:45,336
Oh! Wait. What's with the cane?

146
00:06:45,405 --> 00:06:47,250
Tumor, man. It hurts to walk.

147
00:06:47,274 --> 00:06:50,575
Already? But you were only
diagnosed six months ago.

148
00:06:50,644 --> 00:06:53,445
Did I say months?
I meant years. So...

149
00:06:53,514 --> 00:06:55,847
You must be the wife. Yeah.

150
00:06:55,915 --> 00:06:57,382
Good to meet you.

151
00:06:57,451 --> 00:06:59,501
Good to meet you, too.

152
00:06:59,570 --> 00:07:02,320
Julia went all FSH
on me this morning.

153
00:07:02,388 --> 00:07:03,488
Is that a sexual term?

154
00:07:03,540 --> 00:07:05,356
Wait. You know what?
I don't want to know.

155
00:07:05,426 --> 00:07:07,270
She wants a baby.
She wants my baby.

156
00:07:07,294 --> 00:07:09,027
What did you say?

157
00:07:09,095 --> 00:07:10,762
Nothing. It's crazy.

158
00:07:10,831 --> 00:07:14,210
Until you think about it and
realize it's kind of genius.

159
00:07:14,234 --> 00:07:16,045
I love Julia. I want Sofia to

160
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:17,780
have some siblings
to grow up with.

161
00:07:17,804 --> 00:07:19,044
Why wouldn't I do it?

162
00:07:19,106 --> 00:07:20,783
Are you asking me if
you should have a baby?

163
00:07:20,807 --> 00:07:22,134
What, you think I shouldn't?

164
00:07:22,158 --> 00:07:23,836
Have a baby or ask me if
you should have a baby?

165
00:07:23,860 --> 00:07:25,271
So you think I should do it?

166
00:07:25,295 --> 00:07:27,306
Well, do you want Julia
to be in your life forever?

167
00:07:27,330 --> 00:07:29,008
You think I shouldn't do it?

168
00:07:29,032 --> 00:07:30,552
Do you have to
answer that right now?

169
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:32,416
Hey. Answer what?

170
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:34,536
We were just talking
about the cranioplasty.

171
00:07:35,689 --> 00:07:36,882
Oh, it's exciting, right?

172
00:07:36,906 --> 00:07:38,840
Mm. Yeah.

173
00:07:38,909 --> 00:07:42,327
Charlie Connor, 37. He fell
off the roof six months ago.

174
00:07:42,395 --> 00:07:44,674
He presents for repair
of a skull bone defect

175
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:46,676
that occurred secondary
to surgical removal

176
00:07:46,700 --> 00:07:48,300
of part of his skull.

177
00:07:48,368 --> 00:07:49,629
We waited several
months for the swelling

178
00:07:49,653 --> 00:07:51,564
to subside before...

179
00:07:51,588 --> 00:07:54,089
What were you doing anyway?

180
00:07:54,157 --> 00:07:56,057
Being an idiot.

181
00:07:56,126 --> 00:07:57,303
You gonna fix it next time?

182
00:07:57,327 --> 00:07:59,427
No, I want the roofers
to fix it next time,

183
00:07:59,496 --> 00:08:01,529
like they had
to do it this time,

184
00:08:01,598 --> 00:08:03,982
because Humpty Dumpty
almost killed himself.

185
00:08:04,051 --> 00:08:05,428
You want to pay for it?

186
00:08:05,452 --> 00:08:07,886
Okay, we have
mirrored the healthy skull

187
00:08:07,955 --> 00:08:09,588
and created a
custom titanium plate

188
00:08:09,656 --> 00:08:11,255
that we will secure to the bone.

189
00:08:11,324 --> 00:08:14,542
Titanium. Like The Terminator.

190
00:08:14,611 --> 00:08:17,040
And I'll take fat from the
belly and fill in the gaps,

191
00:08:17,064 --> 00:08:18,491
pull your face into shape.

192
00:08:18,515 --> 00:08:21,966
So, Doc, what are you using to
fasten the new skull into place?

193
00:08:22,035 --> 00:08:23,612
Hexagonal screws? Yes.

194
00:08:23,636 --> 00:08:25,102
You know your stuff.

195
00:08:25,171 --> 00:08:27,383
Yeah, we could do this in my
garage. Save me a few grand.

196
00:08:27,407 --> 00:08:28,718
You got a 2-millimeter bit?

197
00:08:28,742 --> 00:08:30,769
Do I have a 2-millimeter bit?

198
00:08:30,793 --> 00:08:32,844
Please! Don't encourage him.

199
00:08:32,912 --> 00:08:35,013
What? No.

200
00:08:35,082 --> 00:08:37,910
I am counting on you to treat
these candidates extremely well.

201
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:40,379
Show them whatever they
want to see. Really woo them.

202
00:08:40,403 --> 00:08:42,136
"Woo"? Yeah, woo. You know.

203
00:08:42,205 --> 00:08:44,405
What about me says "woo"?

204
00:08:44,474 --> 00:08:45,918
After the boards,
we might be losing

205
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:47,920
some very good doctors
to other programs.

206
00:08:47,944 --> 00:08:49,855
Now, if that happens,
we need to be sure

207
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:51,724
that we have some
fresh talent ready

208
00:08:51,748 --> 00:08:53,258
and willing to take their place,

209
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:54,682
so I am asking you,

210
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:58,269
as Chief, please
woo their socks off.

211
00:09:00,207 --> 00:09:03,424
For you. Just this
once, I will woo.

212
00:09:03,493 --> 00:09:04,758
Their socks off?

213
00:09:04,827 --> 00:09:06,194
Don't push it.

214
00:09:07,297 --> 00:09:08,562
Hi.

215
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:09,964
Hey.

216
00:09:10,033 --> 00:09:12,066
Hey, um, so,

217
00:09:12,135 --> 00:09:14,936
do you have any word on what
Cristina's plans are for next year?

218
00:09:15,004 --> 00:09:16,337
No. No, not yet.

219
00:09:16,405 --> 00:09:19,040
Okay. Will you keep me posted?

220
00:09:20,710 --> 00:09:21,776
I will.

221
00:09:21,844 --> 00:09:22,861
Good. Thanks.

222
00:09:40,130 --> 00:09:42,146
The first session was so easy.

223
00:09:44,885 --> 00:09:47,005
I want to punch your face.

224
00:09:55,811 --> 00:09:56,994
Hey.

225
00:09:57,063 --> 00:10:00,097
Hi. I am so, so
sorry to interrupt.

226
00:10:00,166 --> 00:10:01,967
I'm Dr. Karev.

227
00:10:02,035 --> 00:10:04,515
I was stuck in Seattle
with a patient, and...

228
00:10:04,554 --> 00:10:07,083
Well, I don't want to bore you
with a bunch of travel crap...

229
00:10:07,107 --> 00:10:09,168
Your time was set
for 9:00 this morning.

230
00:10:09,192 --> 00:10:10,687
We were here. We
called your name.

231
00:10:10,711 --> 00:10:12,455
Yeah, I was with a
patient. You get that.

232
00:10:12,479 --> 00:10:16,030
We all have patients,
Dr. Karev. Yet, here we were.

233
00:10:16,099 --> 00:10:18,065
So what? I just fail?

234
00:10:18,134 --> 00:10:20,268
The first of three
sessions, yes.

235
00:10:20,337 --> 00:10:23,505
Which means you need perfect
scores in the next two sessions.

236
00:10:26,643 --> 00:10:28,153
How are you everywhere?

237
00:10:28,177 --> 00:10:30,578
How'd it go for you in there?

238
00:10:30,647 --> 00:10:32,458
Look, baby, I know
you were shocked.

239
00:10:32,482 --> 00:10:33,948
Shocked?

240
00:10:34,017 --> 00:10:36,763
Shocked at the sight
of my mother half-naked

241
00:10:36,787 --> 00:10:38,948
with a senior attending
at my hospital?

242
00:10:38,972 --> 00:10:41,012
No, far from it. Okay?

243
00:10:41,074 --> 00:10:43,519
I mean, it's kind of par for
the course for you, right, Mom?

244
00:10:43,543 --> 00:10:46,506
But every door that I open,
every corner that I turn,

245
00:10:46,530 --> 00:10:47,846
there you are.

246
00:10:47,914 --> 00:10:50,949
I know I'm your mother,
but I'm also a woman.

247
00:10:51,017 --> 00:10:52,450
I have needs.

248
00:10:52,519 --> 00:10:53,963
If you don't want
to talk about this

249
00:10:53,987 --> 00:10:55,381
like an adult,
don't bring it up.

250
00:10:55,405 --> 00:10:56,799
Wait a second. Did I
bring it up? Did I bring it up?

251
00:10:56,823 --> 00:10:58,756
Don't play games.
Just talk to me.

252
00:10:58,825 --> 00:11:02,505
Just leave me alone! I'm in
the middle of my freakin' boards.

253
00:11:04,814 --> 00:11:06,548
Are you following me, Mom?

254
00:11:06,616 --> 00:11:09,384
I'm the examiner in the
room right next to yours.

255
